cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR

The paper discusses the value proposition of academic publishers in coordinating reviews and enhancing text during publication, which is relevant to the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the study compares pre-print papers to their final published versions, which could also be relevant to the fields of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). However, based on the content of the abstract, the first five categories are the most likely.
